          <div class="actions ">
            <div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
              <a href="/flooddonation"> <button type="button" style="border-radius:30px"class="btn  btn-outline-success btn-sm px-3 me-2 fw-semibold" >
                Donate now
              </button></a>
                           
            </div>
            <br>
          </div>  
        </div>
        <br>
      </div>                                  
    </div>     
    
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-body">
        <div class="container marketing">

          <!-- START THE FEATURETTES -->
      
          <div class="row featurette">
            <div class="col-md-7 "style="margin-top:70px;">
              <h1 class="featurette-heading fw-normal lh-1 text-primary">The impact has been almost unimaginable.</h1>
              <p class="lead">City blocks have been almost entirely wiped out, the cities of Hatay and Gaziantep in TÃ¼rkiye are now barely recognisable. With over               <span class="text-danger">85,000 buildings destroyed</span>
              , rescuers were still pulling bodies out of rubble weeks later. Ongoing water and gas cuts make it hard for people to keep warm as temperatures drop below zero during the night. People sheltering in cars and open spaces are at risk from hypothermia.
</p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-5">
              <img class="bd-placeholder-img bd-placeholder-img-lg featurette-image img-fluid mx-auto" width="500" height="500" src="/images/t1.jpeg" alt="">
            </div>
          </div>
      
          <hr class="featurette-divider">
      
          <div class="row featurette">
            <div class="col-md-7 order-md-2 "style="margin-top:70px;">
              <h1 class="featurette-heading fw-normal lh-1 text-primary">
                Turkey-Earthquake: Emergency Situation Report.</span></h1>
              <p class="lead">The United Nations has said at least  <span class="text-danger">1.5 million people</span> have been made homeless in southern Turkey, with more than <span class="text-danger">500,000 homes</span> needing to be rebuilt.

                Nearly <span class="text-danger"> 10,000 aftershocks</span> have been reported since February 6, according to AFAD.
                
